modules.description: Provides functions to read and write Git objects including blobs, trees, commits, and tags, along with pack files and indexes. Supports operations like making pack files position independent and generating index files from pack data. Enables expanding a commit's filesystem and manipulating Git objects through a unified API.

Provides functions for making HTTP GET and POST requests with custom headers and handling errors, operating on `Mimic.ctx` and `Uri.t` types. Includes a pretty-printer for error values and utilities for managing HTTP conduits in a MirageOS environment. Used to interact with remote APIs and manage network communication in embedded or lightweight systems.
